                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#7v #118r" facs="009 119"/> (crude haräg);
                      <locus target="#14v #21v #31v #44v #52v #62v #70r #75r #111v #131r #137v" facs="016 023 033 046 054 064 091 076 113 132 139"/> (a line of alternating red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#38v" facs="040"/> (a line of full stops between lines of alternating red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#140r" facs="141"/> (multiple full stops);
                      <locus target="#150v" facs="152"/> (black dots and lines).
                      A crude section divider in blue ink occurs in the psalms (e.g., ff. <locus target="#1r #14v" facs="002 016"/>)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1">
                      <desc type="Genealogy">
                      <locus target="#152v" facs="154"/> Genealogical list of nine lines, in a later hand
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #138r #138v #151r #151v #152r" facs="001 002 139 140 152 153"/> blank except for a few letters and pen trials
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                      Many of the headings of the Psalter are missing
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#21r #24v #26v #42r" facs="022 026 028 043"/>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#90v #133v" facs="092 135"/>);
                      and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#5r" facs="006"> f. 5r, line 3</locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#13r" facs="014"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces
                      the scribe to reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next
                      line throughout the codex (throughout) But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe
                      completes the line of text above the end of the line (<locus target="#1v #24v #28r" facs="003 026 029"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                    </list>
                  </additions>
